Object 150, referred to as Fiolgine, is an anomalous chemical element originally discovered within [[Level 680]], designated with the chemical symbol Fo.

== History ==
Fiolgine (derived from the Greek word фиолетовый, "violet" in reference to its typical color) was initially discovered in late 2018 along with [[Level 680]] by the temporary [[M.E.G.]] outpost "Five-Minus" which was created for the potential exploitation of resources within the level.

Outpost Five-Minus managed to obtain minor research on Fiolgine, being the ones to name the element and recognize its immense potential as a coolant. The outpost's attempts at directly studying the gas were unsuccessful due to injuries inflicted by the gas due to its poor management, nearly killing one researcher. As a result of this incident, outpost Five-Minus devoted their research to the other properties of [[Level 680]] and thus little information on the properties of the gas were developed.

Only after researchers at [[M.E.G.]] decided to return back to [[Level 680]] with a focus specifically on Fiolgine's potential uses did research reappear, although [[M.E.G.]] never adopted the gas for any significant purposes, likely due to the difficulties in transporting it.

== Characteristics ==
Fiolgine has comparable properties to that of a [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noble_gas| noble gas] as a result of its low chemical reactivity and cryogenic boiling points. Because of its low reactivity, the gas is unable to form stable chemical bonds with other elements even with the presence of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Van_der_Waals_force| van der Waals force] and thus cannot form significant compounds. Fiolgine is inflammable, insoluble in water, non-conductive, and has a low electronegativity.

The most notable feature of Fiolgine is its incredibly high density. In tight enough spaces, this sometimes results in the gas having properties comparable to that of a highly viscous liquid whilst still maintaining gaseous aspects. Because of its density, the gas typically sinks below the air in the area of which it is found in. This often results in the breathable air within the area being quickly displaced, resulting in suffocation and thus asphyxiation. As the gas gathers within the lungs, gas exchange may be impaired, potentially triggering acute [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulmonary_edema| pulmonary edema]. Because of the fact that Fiolgine is typically found at incredibly low temperatures, direct skin contact with it quickly results in [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frostbite| hypothermia]. All handling with Fiolgine should be done with an oxygen mask and tank along with full skin protection.

As a result of its somewhat fluid-like form, Fiolgine tends to gather stagnantly within the hallways of [[Level 680]], creating a literal obstacle to exploration. In the tighter sections of said level, the density may be high enough so that it is possible to "swim" inside of it, although this is only recommended as a last resort if one is cornered by a cloud. In the exterior of the level, most of the gas has settled within various underground sewage systems of the level, therefore making them a non-threat as long as one avoids these sections.

During the event of Aurora Drehnahlis within [[Level 680]], temperatures may drop low enough to produce liquid Fiolgine in areas of the Khrushchyovkas near the level's exterior. The liquid generally poses a lower threat due to it being easily traversed through, although its higher viscosity does still impair movement. Liquid Fiolgine is known to emit gaseous vapors, so long-term exposure to it could prove to be dangerous. When Aurora Drehnahlis is completed, the liquid may take multiple days to return to its gas form.

== Extraction == 
Fiolgine extraction is typically done within areas of the Khrushchyovkas dotting the level, more specifically within the defunct piping systems within them, where Fiolgine gas tends to coagulate. The extraction process generally follows a set procedure:
# A series of pipe containing Fiolgine gas is located, and two holes are cut at different ends.
# At one end of the pipe (preferably one with higher concentration of Fiolgine), a pipe with a funnel connected to a storage tank is inserted into the pipe.
# At the other end of the pipe, hot steam is blown into the pipe, heating up the Fiolgine and pushing the gas into the tank on the other side.
# Once finished, the holes are patched in order to prevent more leakages.
Tanks of Fiolgine can be very heavy when full, so the gas is usually carried away by vehicle whenever possible.

== Applications ==
As a result of the significant difficulty in obtainment, Fiolgine uses are sparse. The [[Republic of Aurielle]] and [[Duchy of Cascada]] have both invested into the establishment of Fiolgine mines for their use as refrigerants, though in recent years these efforts have decreased due to their high cost of transport. In the case of the two groups, Cascada has stockpiled reserves of the gas in order for ease of access for Aurielle, thanks to the cold climate of [[Level 107]].

Fiolgine can prove useful when attempting to nullify or prevent chemical reactions from occurring. This property is useful when dealing with reactive substances where reaction is unfavoured, such as with [[Object 4]] or [[Object 32]].

It has been noted to be possible to create gas-discharge lamps (more commonly referred to as fluorescent light) using Fiolgine, although the density of the gas requires a higher charge to be used to create the effect. This process produces a pinkish glow which may converge into a deeper purple at higher voltages.

It is theorized to be possible to smother fire from [[Object 5]] using Fiolgine, although this has not been tested nor is it likely to. In the case that one is being burned by Object 5, it is recommended to utilize Fiolgine as a last resort if there are no other alternatives.

